<HEADLINE>
<P>
ADMINISTRATION, CONGRESS WRANGLE OVER THE BUDGET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The breakdown of the budget negotiations and its consequences may be my fault. 
</P>
<P>
As a non-voter, Congress does not know or care how I feel on any issue. Well, 
things are going to be different. It is never too late to use our "people" 
power to give notice to the government. I urge all eligible citizens to get off 
their duffs and vote. This is the only way to show politicians that they have 
to take their responsibility to the electorate seriously. 
</P>
<P>
RAY MARRERO, San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
