<HEADLINE>
<P>
ADMINISTRATION, CONGRESS WRANGLE OVER THE BUDGET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How's this for a solution to our budget crisis? Design budgets with two-year 
life spans; have the people vote on them at congressional elections in 
November, and give them three alternative budgets to choose from: one proposed 
by Congress, one proposed by the White House and one proposed by non-elected 
officials from the Treasury and OMB. What a great way to force a deadline on 
our representatives and make them accountable! 
</P>
<P>
PHIL RINEHART, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
