</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The poor health that has been troubling Greg LeMond kept the cyclist out of the 
Paris-Tours race and he will be sidelined for the last two races of the season, 
next week's Tour of Lombardy and the World Cup finale Oct. 27 in Lunel. 
</P>
<P>
Since winning his third Tour de France in July after a long battle to get back 
in shape, LeMond finished fourth in the World Championship, in which he was 
defending champion. 
</P>
<P>
He dropped out of the Grand Prix of the Americas Sept. 30 and recently gave up 
in the first stage of the Tour of Ireland. 
</P>
<P>
LeMond won the Tour de France after a virus and winter promotional activities 
kept him from reaching his peak form until June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
