<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
PEDESTRIAN HIT BY BUS DIES IN HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 48-year-old pedestrian died Sunday from injuries sustained when he was hit by 
a bus, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Jorge Alberto Tobar Santano, of Santa Ana stepped off the north curb at 1600 W. 
1st St. about 5:30 p.m. Saturday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses told police he had stepped off the curb backward, apparently talking 
to someone and facing away from traffic when he was struck by a westbound 
Orange County Transit District bus. He died Sunday morning at Western Medical 
Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
