<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
MEDIGAP INSURANCE DISCUSSION PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A forum to help senior citizens understand private supplemental medical 
insurance and avoid becoming victims of abusive practices is scheduled for 2:30 
to 3:30 p.m. today at the Beverly Manor in Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Called "Consumer Guidelines for Medicare and Long-Term Care Insurance," the 
forum is sponsored by the California Department of Aging's Health Insurance 
Counseling Advocacy Program. 
</P>
<P>
Directors for the advocacy program said the implementation of Medicare 25 years 
ago also opened a market for private Medicare supplementary insurance, called 
Medigap. 
</P>
<P>
"Many feel the insurance industry is taking advantage of individuals living on 
fixed incomes, using hard sales or abusive sales techniques," said Julie 
Schoen, a spokeswoman for the advocacy program. 
</P>
<P>
In the forum, senior citizens will be provided with guidelines to follow when 
purchasing Medigap insurance, as well as long-term care insurance. 
</P>
<P>
The forum is provided free, and those interested in attending can call (714) 
837-8000 for more information. Beverly Manor is at 24452 Health Center Drive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
