<P>
Wild Art 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101590-0062 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 292721 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 15, 1990, Monday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Part F; Page 2; Column 1; Entertainment Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
53 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Grove Shakespeare Festival raised $7,200 Saturday with two fund-raising 
events. A 16K "Walk for William" through Garden Grove drew 50 walkers and 
brought $4,900 in registration fees and pledges, and a sale at the Festival 
Amphitheatre of costumes, masks and props from past productions brought another 
$2,300. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101590-0063 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 292722 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 15, 1990, Monday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
