<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soprano Laurel Boyd, 26, of Laguna Beach took first place from a field of 13 
singers at the Orange County district Metropolitan Opera auditions Saturday at 
Chapman College in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
Second prize went to 32-year-old bass Mel Whitehead of Anaheim. Soprano 
Jennifer Smith, 26, of Tustin came in third, and soprano Carole Sihilling, 32, 
of Laguna Niguel and mezzo-soprano Carter Scott, 27, of Irvine received special 
Encouragement Awards. Boyd, Whitehead and Smith move on to the western regional 
finals, to be held Nov. 8 and 9 at the University of Southern California in Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
