<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: CAMARILLO; 
</P>
<P>
CANDIDATES FORUM PLANNED FOR COUNCIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least seven of the nine candidates for seats on the Camarillo City Council 
have committed themselves to take part in a candidates forum Wednesday, 
according to the Camarillo Chamber of Commerce, the event's sponsor. 
</P>
<P>
Three council seats are at stake in the Nov. 6 election, including that of 
Mayor Charlotte Craven, who is seeking reelection. Incumbents Thomas Martin and 
Sandi Bush are not seeking reelection. 
</P>
<P>
The public is invited to attend the forum, which will be televised on Channel 6 
by Ventura County Cablevision. The forum starts at 7 p.m. in the council 
chambers at City Hall, 601 Carmen Drive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
