<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taiwan Expects to Join Top 10 Traders: The country expects to be among the 10 
largest trading nations by 1996, when its foreign trade should hit nearly $200 
billion, the Board of Foreign Trade said. Last year, Taiwan, with about 20 
million people, ranked 13th in trade, with $66.2 billion in exports and $52.3 
billion in imports. Between 1991 and 1996, its exports are expected to grow an 
average of 7.69% a year, with imports averaging 9.03% growth, said Lee 
Chang-lu, board deputy director. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
