<HEADLINE>
<P>
AT LEAST 20 DIE IN COUNTY IN A WEEKEND OF VIOLENCE; 
</P>
<P>
CRIME: THE VICTIMS INCLUDE A 4-YEAR-OLD BOY AND A GIRL, 16, IN SEPARATE 
INCIDENTS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A weekend of violence left at least 20 people dead and more than a dozen others 
wounded countywide, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's homicide detectives were investigating the apparent murder of an 
elderly woman in La Canada Flintridge. 
</P>
<P>
Neighbors heard gunshots and called deputies, who found the unidentified woman 
dead inside her home in the 600 block of Durwood Drive shortly before 7 p.m. 
Sunday, Lt. Robert Flores said. Deputies held a man and woman found hiding in a 
side yard for questioning, Flores said. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach police were investigating two unrelated stabbing deaths Sunday 
evening. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies were investigating the death of woman whose body was found 
about 6 p.m. Sunday in a pickup truck on Las Virgenes Road in Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
Compton detectives were investigating the death of an unidentified young man in 
the 2600 block of North Parmelee Avenue about 8:30 p.m. Sunday. Police did not 
immediately know how the person died, "but there appears to be some trauma to 
his head," a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
In Inglewood, Jesus Zubia, 24, was booked for investigation of murder after his 
son was shot at their home, although investigators believe the shooting was an 
accident, Police Sgt. Percy Roberts said. 
</P>
<P>
Zubia told officers he thought his .38-caliber revolver was unloaded Friday 
night when he showed it to his two sons, ages 4 and 7, and repeatedly pulled 
the trigger. The gun fired once, and the 4-year-old was shot in the head. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, police hunted for the killers of a cab driver whose body was dumped 
on a street near downtown Los Angeles. Stanley Kolski, 53, was found shot in 
the head Friday evening, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere, a man who refused to share some cocaine was stabbed to death Sunday 
morning in Venice, and in the east county community of Walnut a man was found 
shot to death outside his apartment building, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Seven people were wounded in an apparently gang-related drive-by shooting near 
Los Angeles City College. 
</P>
<P>
A 16-year-old girl was fatally wounded shortly after 1 a.m. Sunday as she rode 
in a car with friends in the Willowbrook area, sheriff's deputies said. People 
in the car had exchanged "gang words" with pedestrians, who opened fire, 
officers said. 
</P>
<P>
Shirley Sandoval, of Los Angeles, died at a nearby hospital. A male suspect, 
whose name was not released, was in custody for investigation of murder, 
officers said. 
</P>
<P>
A drive-by shooting claimed the life of a 19-year-old Los Angeles man early 
Sunday after he was struck by gunfire from a passing car on West 22nd Street. 
</P>
<P>
In Hollywood, one man was killed and another injured in an apartment window 
after exchanging taunts with some people on the street, one of whom pulled a 
gun, police said. There were also shooting deaths at a Highland Park 
intersection and near a Los Angeles hamburger stand. 
</P>
<P>
Six other people died in weekend violence previously reported by The Times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
