<P>
IBM PROFIT RISES 27% FOR QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
IBM said today that its profit jumped nearly 27% in the third quarter despite 
weakening economic conditions at home and abroad. 
</P>
<P>
International Business Machines Corp. said net income for the three months 
ended Sept. 30 totaled $1.11 billion, or $1.95 a share, up from $877 million, 
or $1.51 a share, in the same quarter last year. Revenue rose nearly 7%, to 
$15.28 billion, from $14.30 billion in the year-ago period. 
</P>
<P>
Overall sales slipped 1.5%, to $9.01 billion, but revenue derived from support 
services, software, equipment rental and financing posted double-digit 
increases over the year-earlier period. 
</P>
<P>
The earnings were slightly below the expectations of industry analysts. 
</P>
